#Genome Assembly Pipeline and Github links for all software
#1 convert raw ONT fast5 into pod5 file type 
(pod5-file-format tool) - https://github.com/nanoporetech/pod5-file-format
#2 basecall the pod5 files into sequences using dorado duplex basecaller 
dorado - https://github.com/nanoporetech/dorado/
#3 Samtools to convert bam to fastq file format 
Samtools - https://github.com/samtools/samtools
#3 NanoPlot (1.33) to assess read sets 
 NanoPlot-  https://github.com/wdecoster/NanoPlot
#3 Use porechop_abi to trim and split reads of adaptors 
Porechop_abi - https://github.com/bonsai-team/Porechop_ABI
#4 qulaity control and subset reads based on quality and length  
Chopper - https://github.com/wdecoster/chopper
#5 feed these QC'd datasets into an assembler (Canu and Flye) 
Canu  = https://github.com/marbl/canu, Flye = https://github.com/fenderglass/Flye
#6 draft genome assembly quality assessment using BUSCO, Quast and Findtelomeres.py 
https://github.com/JanaSperschneider/FindTelomeres
https://busco.ezlab.org/busco_userguide.html
https://github.com/ablab/quast
#7 iterate draft assembly through a genome polishing tool (medaka)
https://github.com/nanoporetech/medaka
